            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">As 
              always, the road to becoming a member is not a short one. You must 
              prove to us that you are dedicated to our cause and that you possess 
              the skills and aptitudes we are looking for.</font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">You 
              must let us know of your interest in joining by posting in our <a href="http://pub48.ezboard.com/feternusastralis25155frm6">Recruitment 
              Requests section</a> on our <a href="http://pub48.ezboard.com/beternusastralis25155">message 
              board</a>. Be sure to tell us about yourself, about why you want 
              to join EA and how you think you would contribute to bettering our 
              guild. </font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">After 
              posting, get to know us, make friends in the guild, make a name 
              for yourself. </font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">When 
              we feel you are known enough and have the right attitude, we will 
              move your application to our private section for the vote. Our recruiting 
              officer, will create a post in our members section where members 
              will have one week (1 week) to vote. <u>A minimum</u> of <i><b>25 
              sponsors</b></i> are required to pass with <i>no more than</i> <b><i>5 
              votes against</i></b>. After the 1 week period, Our recruiting officer 
              will inform you on the outcome of the vote. </font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">1. 
              If you do not pass the vote because you have more than <i><b>5 votes 
              against</b></i>, that usually means you have some issues to work 
              out with a few members before being able to reapply. You will not 
              be able to reapply for a period of 2 months.</font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">2. 
              If you do not pass the vote because you have less than <i><b>25 
              sponsors</b></i> *and* you have <i>no more than <b>5 votes against</b></i>, 
              this usually means not enough people know you and you must continue 
              to make friends in the guild and make yourself known to our members. 
              You will be able to reapply in 3 weeks time. </font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><img src="img/button.gif" width="20" height="14"> 
              <font color="#FF9900">Minimum Requirements</font></font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Eternus 
              Astralis requires the following to even be considered for membership 
              : </font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">1. 
              You must be of a <u><b>minimum level of 57</b></u> (unless stated 
              otherwise, see above chart).<br>
              2. You must attend a minimum of <b>20 raids</b> with EA (raid of 
              3 groups or more).<br>
              3. You must have Ruins of Kunark and Scars of Velious.<br>
              4. You must have your Sebilis Key.<br>
              5. You must have a minimum of <b>25 members</b> ready to sponsor 
              you.<br>
              6. You must have <b>no more</b> than <b>5 votes</b> against.</font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><br>
              7. You must be working on your Veeshan`s Peak Key Quest.<br>
              </font> </p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><img src="img/button.gif" width="20" height="14"> 
              <font color="#FF9900">Important Requirement</font></font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">We 
              oblige all prospects to work out any problems or conflicts they 
              may have with current Eternus Astralis members. Preservation of 
              harmony between guildmates is imperative to our success and achievement 
              of our goals. Thus, if a prospect is seen has having too many conflicts* 
              with existing members, the prospect will not receive an invitation 
              (even if the minimum requirements are met) until the conflicts are 
              worked out.</font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><img src="img/button.gif" width="20" height="14"> 
              <font color="#FF9800">The "MORTAL ENEMY" clause </font></font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">If 
              a candidate has wronged an Eternus Astralis member to the point 
              where if that candidate were to join the current member would leave, 
              that candidate cannot continue in the process. Eternus Astralis 
              has built our tight family atmosphere by being, well, a tight knit 
              family. Officers will ALWAYS side with the guild in these kinds 
              of matters. It should be noted however that invocation of this clause 
              requires an investigation into the situation between the candidate 
              and the member, and is not to be used lightly. Abuse of this clause 
              is against Eternus Astralis policy and carries with it heavy consequences 
              (suspension, guild removal). </font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><img src="img/button.gif" width="20" height="14"> 
              <font color="#FF9900"></font></font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color="#FF9900">Provisional 
              Membership</font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> If 
              the candidate has met the above criteria, then the candidate is 
              invited to the guild by either the Admissions Officer (Linxs) or 
              the Guild Leader (Rovell). He/she will have access to our guild 
              tag, chat, and private message board. As a provisional member, they 
              are on a one (1) month probational term. During this probationary 
              period the new member is required to do the following: </font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">1. 
              Disband from their current guild (if applicable). <br>
              2. Acquire resistance gear (100 for all resistances, not concurrently) 
              <br>
              3. Acquire a water-breathing device (or have the ability to cast 
              the appropriate spell). <br>
              4. Learn and follow guild policy. <br>
              5. Attend scheduled raids (if they are online). <br>
              6. Attend scheduled guild meetings (unless RL circumstances do not 
              allow). </font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Failure 
              to meet these requirements at the end of the one month term is grounds 
              for dismissal. </font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><img src="img/button.gif" width="20" height="14"> 
              <font color="#FF9900"></font></font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color="#FF9900">Communique</font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> Prospective 
              members are NOT permitted to use the Eternus Astralis guild tag 
              in any public posts during their probational period. They are also 
              NOT permitted to post any derogatory or defaming comments about 
              any player or guild without the express permission of the guild 
              leader. Violation of this policy is grounds for immediate dismissal. 
              </font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><img src="img/button.gif" width="20" height="14"> 
              </font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color="#FF9900">Full 
              Membership </font></p>
            <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> Full 
              membership is granted to a new member at the end of the one month 
              period provided they have met the above requirements. </font></p>
